Key Match Events: Habib Diallo netted in the 27th minute for Senegal
Namibia had the ball in the net after 14 minutes, but the goal was disallowed due to minimal contact with the goalkeeper
Post-Match Reflections: Senegal are one point above Sudan and the Democratic Republic of Congo in the group standings
Tunisia have a two-point lead in Group H over Namibia with Liberia a further point back in third place
Miscellaneous Highlights: A lengthy delay occurred in the Senegal vs Mauritania match after frustrated home fans threw objects towards the pitch in the second half
Sao Tome have lost all four of their qualifiers in Group H
Djibouti gained their first point in Group A in a 1-1 draw with neighbours Ethiopia
Others: Senegal and Tunisia are fancied to qualify again for the 2026 World Cup
The four best runners-up will have a chance to advance through two series of playoff tournaments
